[ctns_make id='gen_alg_logic_statements']

  [ctns_front style='']
Logic Statements
  [/ctns_front]  

  [ctns_back style='width:80%;font-size:80%;']
<div> <div style='float:left;text-align:right'> statement:<br/> contrapositive:<br/> converse:<br/> inverse: </div> <div> $$p \implies q$$<br/> $$\neg q \implies \neg p$$<br/> $$q \implies p$$<br/> $$\neg p \implies \neg q$$ </div> </div>
  [/ctns_back]  

  [ctns_backspeak]
For well-formed formulas P and Q, -- Let a statement read as -- P implies Q, -- The contrapositive to this statement reads negative Q implies negative P, -- the converse to this statements reads Q implies P, -- And finally, the inverse to this statement reads negative P implies negative Q.
  [/ctns_backspeak]  

[/ctns_make]
